<p align="center" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="5"><b>Installation</b></font></p>
<p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4"> To install the Teacher 
Tool just follow the directions specified in the Readme file of the Teacher Tool 
directory(also shown below).</font></p>
<p align="left" style="line-height: 150%">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4">Sun Java SDK Installation<br>
----------------------------------<br>
* Please make sure a Java SDK, or JRE are installed before running<br>
the Teacher Tool.<br>
* Follow the directions at Sun's website for installing the Java software.<br>
* Make sure to set your path correctly!<br>
<br>
Starting Java Teacher Tool<br>
----------------------------------<br>
* Make sure to run the Java Teacher Tool from the directory that contains<br>
the images directory, library directory, and the files config_teacher.ini <br>
and config_facealive.ini.<br>
* The file config_teacher.ini specifies the name server. For example the<br>
host for Pitt is adam.cs.pitt.edu and the port number is 2020. The file<br>
config_facealivep.ini specifies the image server. For example the host <br>
for Pitt is adam.cs.pitt.edu and the port number is 7654.<br>
* Double click TeacherTool410.jar to begin the program, or from the<br>
command line from inside the Java Teacher Tool V4 directory type <br>
java -jar TeacherTool410.jar</font></p>

